DURBAN: Two children were killed and another injured after they were struck by a minibus taxi and a vehicle in separate accidents in KwaZulu-Natal on Friday. Emer-G-Med Paramedics spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said a 15-year-old boy was killed after he was struck by a minibus taxi while attempting to cross Chris Hani Road in the Avoca area in Durban. He said the incident occurred  just after 6pm on Friday night. Van Reenen said when paramedics arrived on the scene they found the boy lying in the road. The 15-year-old suffered fatal injuries, he said. “He was declared dead on the scene,” said Van Reenen. Meanwhile, on the same night in Pietermaritzburg, Mi7 National Group Emergency Medical Services spokesperson Colin Davids said two children were struck by a vehicle in an alleged hit-and-run.   Davids said emergency services were dispatched after reports of a motor vehicle accident involving pedestrians on Mayors Walk Road. “Mi7 medics found a 5-year-old boy had already succumbed to his injuries and was declared deceased on scene,” he said. He said the second victim, a 10-year-old girl was left with minor injuries and transported to hospital by another service provider. “It is believed that both children were crossing the road when they were struck by a vehicle,”he said. Davids said the driver fled the scene. “We pass our condolences to the loved ones of the deceased,” said Davids. MOST READ: – Vehicle hijacked in PMB found in KZN South Coast chop shop, suspects dropped victim off in Cato Manor – Durban Solid Waste worker dies in truck accident while on duty – Teen sisters speak of trauma after being raped during KZN house robbery, one of the rapists handed hefty sentence – eThekwini Water and Sanitation clerk, two service providers nabbed for fraud – Black mamba rescued in the parking lot of Westville office park THE MERCURY